HEADWORD: Anthraquinone
<hw>An`thra*qui"none</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Anthra</ets>cene + <ets>quinone</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A hydrocarbon, <chform>C6H4.C2O2.C6H4</chform>,
subliming in shining yellow needles. It is obtained by oxidation of
anthracene.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

